## "Anatomy" — Defined

When any rule says "read anatomy" or "anatomy first", this is exactly what that means:

```
1. List root directory
2. Read STRUCTURE.md if it exists
3. Read package.json / pyproject.toml / go.mod (whichever exists)
4. Scan: src/, app/, lib/, components/ — list, don't read
5. Check .venom/CONTEXT.md if present
```

Not a file-by-file walk. A structural read. Takes 30-60 seconds. Required before multi-file work.

